    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er76e] Erd\\H{o}s, P., Problems and results on consecutive integers. Publ. Math. Debrecen (1976), 271-282.\n \n [RST75b] Ramachandra, K. and Shorey, T. N. and Tijdeman, R., On {G}rimm's problem relating to factorisation of a block of\nconsecutive integers. {II}. J. Reine Angew. Math. (1976), 192--201.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er76e} proved that, for every $\\alpha>1$, if $k$ is sufficiently large and $n>k^\\alpha-k$ then\\[f(n,k) > \\left(1-\\frac{1}{\\alpha}+c_\\alpha\\right)k\\]for some constant $c_\\alpha>0$, and if $1<\\alpha<2$ and $n\\leq k^\\alpha-k$ then\\[f(n,k) < (\\alpha-1+o(1))k.\\]He knew of no non-trivial bounds when $\\alpha \\geq 2$.\n\nRamachandra, Shorey, and Tijdeman \\cite{RST75b} proved that if $n>\\exp(c(\\log k)^2)$ for a constant $c>0$ then $f(n,k)\\geq k-\\pi(k)$."
    },
